OL,3,CSouth East Water to undergo 'MOT' as
OL,4,Cplans for new regulator unveiled
OL,6,FCurrently, Ofwat oversees how much
OL,7,Fwater companies in England and Wales
OL,8,Fcan charge for services; the Drinking
OL,9,FWater Inspectorate ensures that public
OL,10,Fwater supplies are safe; while the
OL,11,FEnvironment Agency and Natural England
OL,12,Fhave regulatory functions to monitor
OL,13,Ffirms' impact on nature.
OL,15,FThe regulators have faced intense
OL,16,Fcriticism for overseeing companies
OL,17,Fduring years when they paid out to
OL,18,Fshareholders and accrued large debts,
OL,19,Fwhile ageing infrastructure crumbled
OL,20,Fand sewage spills skyrocketed.
